description.narrative: By the end of 2020, over 500,000 people in the UNICEF supported five focus districts have improved availability of and increased demand for high impact nutrition interventions., which contributes to Community-Based Management Of Acute Malnutrition, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Infant And Young Child Feeding, Micronutrients, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020, reduced child mortality and under-nutrition through improved and equitable use of high impact health, nutrition and WASH interventions.

description.narrative: In 2020, UNICEF maintained similar strategies to support the nutrition program. Access to nutrition services was enhanced by ensuring delivery of quality nutrition services and availability of essential nutrition supplies for prevention and treatment of severe acute malnutrition. UNICEF also supported the Ministry of Health (MOH) through the nutrition department for the coordination of nutrition program. Continued support was provided with the development of strategies and legislation for improvement of nutrition outcomes and to protect, promote and support infant and young child feeding (IYCF) practices. These strategies were strengthened by the community mobilization for behavior change in favor of nutrition. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:03/02/2021
